Chapter 2 Introduction The Multiple-Institution Database for Investigating Engineering Longitudinal Development (MIDFIELD) is a student record data set for studying how undergraduate students maneuver through their curricula (Ohland and Long 2016). The MIDFIELD database includes approximately one million undergraduate students at sixteen US institutions from 1987 to 2016. The R package midfieldr and its associated data packages provide a stratified sample of MIDFIELD data: registrarsâ€™ student records for 98,000 undergraduate students with proportional representation by institution, program, transfer status, sex, and race/ethnicity.
